Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specify_cell_virtual_align(25.10)            specify_cell_virtual_align(25.10)

Name
       specify_cell_virtual_align  -  Aligns  a filler cell that does not have
       any pin or obs geometries to align, but the  cell  still  needs  to  be
       aligned

Syntax
        specify_cell_virtual_align

       [-help]

       [-cell <cells>]

       [-mask <id>]

       [-pin_x_loc <microns>]

       Aligns  a  filler  cell that does not have any pin or obs geometries to
       align, but the cell still needs to be aligned. For example, a GA-Filler
       cell after the post-mask ECO becomes a logic cell and needs to be  cor-
       rectly aligned for the router to eco-route it.

       The  specify_cell_virtual_align command can be used to provide mask for
       the first track inside the cell, or `offset' to  the  first  track  (or
       both). You need to specify -mask or -pin_x_loc.

       The  command  auto-detects  the layer for vertical alignment. If as per
       the placement initialization there is no need  for  vertical  alignment
       (site-width   and  vertical-track-pitch  are  same,  pin-mask  are  not
       fixed), the virtual alignment is turned off. this means that the  spec-
       ify_cell_virtual_align command will not help.

Parameters
       -cell <cells>
              Specifies the lib-cells with virtual alignment requirement.

              -help"  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and de-
              fault information for each specify_cell_virtual_align parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specify_cell_virtual_align

       -mask <virtual_mask_value>
              Specifies the virtual mask value for  the  first  track  in  the
              cell.

              If  you specify -mask only, the offset of the first track in the
              core is used as the offset.

       -pin_x_loc <location_in_microns>
              Specifies the location of the virtual  geometry  from  the  cell
              boundary.

              If  you specify offset only, the track can be of any mask-color,
              as long as offset matches.

              Default: First track location

